               <p>JOHN THOMAS. I am an <rs id="t18300916-317-viclabel1630" type="occupation">auctioneer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-317-victim2605 t18300916-317-viclabel1630"></join>. On the 29th of July I lost a pair of pistols from <placeName id="t18300916-317-crimeloc1631">Eccleston-street, Pimlico</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-317-crimeloc1631" type="placeName" value="Eccleston-street, Pimlico"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-317-crimeloc1631" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-317-off1628 t18300916-317-crimeloc1631"></join> - I had not seen them for some time; they were deposited with me, with other property, for sale by auction - I took possession of the house and property three or four days before the sale; I know they were there, from the inventory and catalogue - I do not know the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-317-person2606">
                  FREDERICK 
                  JACKSON
               <interp inst="t18300916-317-person2606" type="surname" value="JACKSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-317-person2606" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-317-person2606" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter, and live in Phoenix-street, Soho. I have seen the prisoner at different sales; the furniture was for sale on that day - I tied a pair of pistols to each of two blunderbusses; I did not particularly notice them - I had occasion to go down from the second floor, and I asked my fellow-servant whether any body was in the house; he said No; I went up again, and missed one pistol from each blunderbuss - I went out, and took the prisoner a quarter of a mile from the house, with something wrapped up in a blue handkerchief under his arm; I said, "I want the pistols;" I opened the parcel, and they were in it - I gave him to the Policeman; he begged I would let him go - I said I would not, as I had been robbed so many times.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-317-person2607">
                  WILLIAM 
                  AGGS
               <interp inst="t18300916-317-person2607" type="surname" value="AGGS"></interp>
